## Common Commands
```bash
# Development
docker compose up -d                          # Start all services
docker compose logs -f bot                    # Tail bot logs
docker compose exec bot python -c "..."       # Run command in bot container
docker compose restart bot                    # Restart bot only

# Production deploy
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml \
               -f docker-compose.prod.yml \
               up -d --build                  # Build and start

# Run ML training manually
docker compose --profile training run trainer # One-off training run

# Maintenance
docker compose down                           # Stop all
docker system prune -f                        # Clean unused images/containers
docker compose exec db psql -U kalshi_bot -d kalshi  # DB shell

# View resource usage
docker stats

# Check health
docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' kalshi-bot
```

## Systemd Service (Auto-start on Reboot)
```ini
# /etc/systemd/system/kalshi-bot.service
[Unit]
Description=Kalshi Trading Bot
Requires=docker.service
After=docker.service network-online.target

[Service]
Type=oneshot
RemainAfterExit=yes
WorkingDirectory=/home/botuser/kalshi-bot
ExecStart=/usr/bin/docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
ExecStop=/usr/bin/docker compose down
TimeoutStartSec=300
User=botuser

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

```bash
# Enable auto-start
sudo systemctl enable kalshi-bot
sudo systemctl start kalshi-bot
sudo systemctl status kalshi-bot
```

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
- **Running containers as root**: Always set a non-root USER in your Dockerfile
- **Committing .env files**: Add .env to .gitignore immediately — rotate any keys that were exposed
- **No restart policy**: Set `restart: unless-stopped` on the bot container — it must survive reboots
- **Missing health checks**: Without health checks, Docker won't know your bot silently crashed
- **Bloated images**: Use slim/alpine base images and multi-stage builds to keep image sizes small
- **No log rotation**: Set `max-size` and `max-file` on all logging configs — unrotated logs fill disk fast
- **Database in same container as bot**: Always separate DB into its own service (or use DO Managed DB in prod)
